list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: updated online set checks to also check

task.summary: updating to only look for artists at the moment for a smaller and more manageable service
updated souring of nf_SHINV and tags for nf_upeur
updated mtgjson scraper to use requests.json() method rather than reading the raw page content into a new json with with the json library. Seems to work a bit faster also due to cutting down the size
large refactoring to make code base more program / user orientated rather than the current developer orientated set up I originally started with.
updated to better use requests module functionality
updated to remove clutter from print statements and cleaned up the return statement
trimmed down clutter further in the file
removed testing limit, added further comments
combined all working scripts into singular file which can be run from standard terminal

Updated scraper to run using multiprocessing module this allows for the MTDATA file to be generated within ~10 minutes rather than the hour it was taking before.
Multithreading not disallowed on the site's robots.txt file
MTGJSON updated keywords (will make benchmarking easier) and changed layout of website
very rough work to merge old cons file to updated total cons list. Needs much more work and will probbly be phased out to SQL variant
old files that need to be optimised because sloooooow as hell
added functionality to also check set listings on mkm incase updates to the mapping are needed

MKM updated their webpage so had to update the tags the scraper was pointing at.
Works fine now and generates file for 20190319
Modern Horizons added by MKM but not listed on MTGJSON

updated online set checks to also check mtgjson as well as mkm.
both set lists are now stored within one json file rather than storing in separate text documents

As mtgjson has a built in mapping to TCGPLAYER, I'm going to swap the project from market weighted benchmarks to price weighted benchmarks.
This is still a valid technique and will hopefully allow for a greater purity in mapping than attempting to map a limited subset of cards to their correpsonding mkm card.
updated price source to be TCGPLAYER.com
forgot to remove test limiter... fixed now
no need to monitor online mapping as tcg maping is built into mtgjson
updating crawl delay in the tcg scraper
